  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'This message was given to Amos, a shepherd from the town of Tekoa
        in Judah. He received this message in visions two years before the earthquake,
        when Uzziah was king of Judah and Jeroboam II, the son of Jehoash,[COMMENT[0]]
        was king of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Joash, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoash.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "This is what he saw and heard:\n\t\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        voice will roar from Zion\n\tand thunder from Jerusalem!\n\tThe lush pastures
        of the shepherds will dry up;\n\tthe grass on Mount Carmel will wither and
        die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "God\u2019s Judgment on Israel\u2019s Neighbors"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Damascus have sinned again and again,[COMMENT[0]]and I will not let them
        go unpunished!\n\tThey beat down my people in Gilead\n\tas grain is threshed
        with iron sledges.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'have committed three sins, even four; '
        - ft: also in 1:6, 9, 11, 13.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on King Hazael\u2019s palace,\n\tand the
        fortresses of King Ben-hadad will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will break down the gates of Damascus\n\tand slaughter the people
        in the valley of Aven.\n\tI will destroy the ruler in Beth-eden,\n\tand the
        people of Aram will go as captives to Kir,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Gaza have sinned again and again,\n\tand I will not let them go unpunished!\n\tThey
        sent whole villages into exile,\n\tselling them as slaves to Edom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on the walls of Gaza,\n\tand all its fortresses
        will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will slaughter the people of Ashdod\n\tand destroy the king of
        Ashkelon.\n\tThen I will turn to attack Ekron,\n\tand the few Philistines
        still left will be killed,\u201D\n\tsays the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Tyre have sinned again and again,\n\tand I will not let them go unpunished!\n\tThey
        broke their treaty of brotherhood with Israel,\n\tselling whole villages
        as slaves to Edom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on the walls of Tyre,\n\tand all its fortresses
        will be destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Edom have sinned again and again,\n\tand I will not let them go unpunished!\n\tThey
        chased down their relatives, the Israelites, with swords,\n\tshowing them
        no mercy.\n\tIn their rage, they slashed them continually\n\tand were unrelenting
        in their anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on Teman,\n\tand the fortresses of Bozrah
        will be destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Ammon have sinned again and again,\n\tand I will not let them go unpunished!\n\tWhen
        they attacked Gilead to extend their borders,\n\tthey ripped open pregnant
        women with their swords.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on the walls of Rabbah,\n\tand all its fortresses
        will be destroyed.\n\tThe battle will come upon them with shouts,\n\tlike
        a whirlwind in a mighty storm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And their king[COMMENT[0]] and his princes will go into exile together,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t."
      comments:
      - number: '1:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'malcam, '
        - ft: possibly referring to their god Molech.
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Moab have sinned again and again,[COMMENT[0]]and I will not let them go
        unpunished!\n\tThey desecrated the bones of Edom\u2019s king,\n\tburning
        them to ashes.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'have committed three sins, even four; '
        - ft: also in 2:4, 6.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on the land of Moab,\n\tand all the fortresses
        in Kerioth will be destroyed.\n\tThe people will fall in the noise of battle,\n\tas
        the warriors shout and the ram\u2019s horn sounds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will destroy their king\n\tand slaughter all their princes,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "God\u2019s Judgment on Judah and Israel"
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Judah have sinned again and again,\n\tand I will not let them go unpunished!\n\tThey
        have rejected the instruction of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\trefusing
        to obey his decrees.\n\tThey have been led astray by the same lies\n\tthat
        deceived their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send down fire on Judah,\n\tand all the fortresses of Jerusalem
        will be destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThe people
        of Israel have sinned again and again,\n\tand I will not let them go unpunished!\n\tThey
        sell honorable people for silver\n\tand poor people for a pair of sandals.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They trample helpless people in the dust\n\tand shove the oppressed
        out of the way.\n\tBoth father and son sleep with the same woman,\n\tcorrupting
        my holy name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At their religious festivals,\n\tthey lounge in clothing their debtors
        put up as security.\n\tIn the house of their gods,[COMMENT[0]]they drink
        wine bought with unjust fines.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: their God.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut as my people watched,\n\tI destroyed the Amorites,\n\tthough
        they were as tall as cedars\n\tand as strong as oaks.\n\tI destroyed the
        fruit on their branches\n\tand dug out their roots.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It was I who rescued you from Egypt\n\tand led you through the desert
        for forty years,\n\tso you could possess the land of the Amorites.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I chose some of your sons to be prophets\n\tand others to be Nazirites.\n\tCan
        you deny this, my people of Israel?\u201D\n\tasks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you caused the Nazirites to sin by making them drink wine,\n\tand
        you commanded the prophets, \u2018Shut up!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo I will make you groan\n\tlike a wagon loaded down with sheaves
        of grain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your fastest runners will not get away.\n\tThe strongest among you
        will become weak.\n\tEven mighty warriors will be unable to save themselves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The archers will not stand their ground.\n\tThe swiftest runners
        won\u2019t be fast enough to escape.\n\tEven those riding horses won\u2019t
        be able to save themselves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On that day the most courageous of your fighting men\n\twill drop
        their weapons and run for their lives,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to this message that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken
        against you, O people of Israel\u2014against the entire family I rescued
        from Egypt:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFrom among all the families on the earth,\n\tI have been intimate
        with you alone.\n\tThat is why I must punish you\n\tfor all your sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Witnesses against Guilty Israel
      content: "Can two people walk together\n\twithout agreeing on the direction?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does a lion ever roar in a thicket\n\twithout first finding a victim?\n\tDoes
        a young lion growl in its den\n\twithout first catching its prey?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does a bird ever get caught in a trap\n\tthat has no bait?\n\tDoes
        a trap spring shut\n\twhen there\u2019s nothing to catch?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the ram\u2019s horn blows a warning,\n\tshouldn\u2019t the people
        be alarmed?\n\tDoes disaster come to a city\n\tunless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has planned it?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Indeed, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> never does anything\n\tuntil
        he reveals his plans to his servants the prophets.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lion has roared\u2014\n\tso who isn\u2019t frightened?\n\tThe
        Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken\u2014\n\tso who can refuse
        to proclaim his message?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Announce this to the leaders of Philistia[COMMENT[0]]and to the great
        ones of Egypt:\n\t\u201CTake your seats now on the hills around Samaria,\n\tand
        witness the chaos and oppression in Israel.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Ashdod.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy people have forgotten how to do right,\u201D\n\tsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CTheir fortresses are filled with
        wealth\n\ttaken by theft and violence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore,\u201D says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Can
        enemy is coming!\n\tHe will surround them and shatter their defenses.\n\tThen
        he will plunder all their fortresses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CA shepherd
        who tries to rescue a sheep from a lion\u2019s mouth\n\twill recover only
        two legs or a piece of an ear.\n\tSo it will be for the Israelites in Samaria
        lying on luxurious beds,\n\tand for the people of Damascus reclining on couches.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew in this sentence is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow listen to this, and announce it throughout all Israel,[COMMENT[0]]\u201D
        says the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the house of Jacob. '
        - ft: "The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged
            throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes to the individual patriarch
            and sometimes to the nation."
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn the very day I punish Israel for its sins,\n\tI will destroy
        the pagan altars at Bethel.\n\tThe horns of the altar will be cut off\n\tand
        fall to the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will destroy the beautiful homes of the wealthy\u2014\n\ttheir
        winter mansions and their summer houses, too\u2014\n\tall their palaces filled
        with ivory,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Failure to Learn"
      content: "Listen to me, you fat cows[COMMENT[0]]living in Samaria,\n\tyou women
        who oppress the poor\n\tand crush the needy,\n\tand who are always calling
        to your husbands,\n\t\u201CBring us another drink!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: you cows of Bashan.
    - title: 
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn this by his holiness:\n\t\u201CThe
        time will come when you will be led away\n\twith hooks in your noses.\n\tEvery
        last one of you will be dragged away\n\tlike a fish on a hook!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be led out through the ruins of the wall;\n\tyou will be
        thrown from your fortresses,[COMMENT[0]]\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'thrown out toward Harmon, '
        - ft: possibly a reference to Mount Hermon.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo ahead and offer sacrifices to the idols at Bethel.\n\tKeep
        on disobeying at Gilgal.\n\tOffer sacrifices each morning,\n\tand bring your
        tithes every three days.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Present your bread made with yeast\n\tas an offering of thanksgiving.\n\tThen
        give your extra voluntary offerings\n\tso you can brag about it everywhere!\n\tThis
        is the kind of thing you Israelites love to do,\u201D\n\tsays the Sovereign
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI brought hunger to every city\n\tand famine to every town.\n\tBut
        still you would not return to me,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI kept the rain from falling\n\twhen your crops needed it the
        most.\n\tI sent rain on one town\n\tbut withheld it from another.\n\tRain
        fell on one field,\n\twhile another field withered away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People staggered from town to town looking for water,\n\tbut there
        was never enough.\n\tBut still you would not return to me,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI struck your farms and vineyards with blight and mildew.\n\tLocusts
        devoured all your fig and olive trees.\n\tBut still you would not return
        to me,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI sent plagues on you\n\tlike the plagues I sent on Egypt long
        ago.\n\tI killed your young men in war\n\tand led all your horses away.[COMMENT[0]]The
        stench of death filled the air!\n\tBut still you would not return to me,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: and slaughtered your captured horses.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI destroyed some of your cities,\n\tas I destroyed[COMMENT[0]]
        Sodom and Gomorrah.\n\tThose of you who survived\n\twere like charred sticks
        pulled from a fire.\n\tBut still you would not return to me,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: as when God destroyed.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, I will bring upon you all the disasters I have announced.\n\tPrepare
        to meet your God in judgment, you people of Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the one who shaped the mountains,\n\tstirs
        up the winds, and reveals his thoughts to mankind.\n\tHe turns the light
        of dawn into darkness\n\tand treads on the heights of the earth.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies is his name!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: 'Listen, you people of Israel! Listen to this funeral song I am singing:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe virgin Israel has fallen,\n\tnever to rise again!\n\tShe
        lies abandoned on the ground,\n\twith no one to help her up.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CWhen a city
        sends a thousand men to battle,\n\tonly a hundred will return.\n\tWhen a
        town sends a hundred,\n\tonly ten will come back alive.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to the family
        of Israel:\n\t\u201CCome back to me and live!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t worship at the pagan altars at Bethel;\n\tdon\u2019t go
        to the shrines at Gilgal or Beersheba.\n\tFor the people of Gilgal will be
        dragged off into exile,\n\tand the people of Bethel will be reduced to nothing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come back to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and live!\n\tOtherwise,
        he will roar through Israel[COMMENT[0]] like a fire,\n\tdevouring you completely.\n\tYour
        gods in Bethel\n\twon\u2019t be able to quench the flames.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the house of Joseph.
    - title: 
      content: "You twist justice, making it a bitter pill for the oppressed.\n\tYou
        treat the righteous like dirt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who created the stars,\n\tthe
        Pleiades and Orion.\n\tHe turns darkness into morning\n\tand day into night.\n\tHe
        draws up water from the oceans\n\tand pours it down as rain on the land.\n\tThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is his name!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "With blinding speed and power he destroys the strong,\n\tcrushing
        all their defenses.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How you hate honest judges!\n\tHow you despise people who tell the
        truth!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You trample the poor,\n\tstealing their grain through taxes and unfair
        rent.\n\tTherefore, though you build beautiful stone houses,\n\tyou will
        never live in them.\n\tThough you plant lush vineyards,\n\tyou will never
        drink wine from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I know the vast number of your sins\n\tand the depth of your
        rebellions.\n\tYou oppress good people by taking bribes\n\tand deprive the
        poor of justice in the courts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So those who are smart keep their mouths shut,\n\tfor it is an evil
        time.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do what is good and run from evil\n\tso that you may live!\n\tThen
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies will be your
        helper,\n\tjust as you have claimed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hate evil and love what is good;\n\tturn your courts into true halls
        of justice.\n\tPerhaps even yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies\n\twill have mercy on the remnant of his people.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the remnant of Joseph.
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies, says:\n\t\u201CThere will be crying in all the
        public squares\n\tand mourning in every street.\n\tCall for the farmers to
        weep with you,\n\tand summon professional mourners to wail.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There will be wailing in every vineyard,\n\tfor I will destroy them
        all,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Warning of Coming Judgment
      content: "What sorrow awaits you who say,\n\t\u201CIf only the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        were here!\u201D\n\tYou have no idea what you are wishing for.\n\tThat day
        will bring darkness, not light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day you will be like a man who runs from a lion\u2014\n\tonly
        to meet a bear.\n\tEscaping from the bear, he leans his hand against a wall
        in his house\u2014\n\tand he\u2019s bitten by a snake.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be dark and
        hopeless,\n\twithout a ray of joy or hope.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI hate all your show and pretense\u2014\n\tthe hypocrisy of
        your religious festivals and solemn assemblies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will not accept your burnt offerings and grain offerings.\n\tI
        won\u2019t even notice all your choice peace offerings.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Away with your noisy hymns of praise!\n\tI will not listen to the
        music of your harps.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, I want to see a mighty flood of justice,\n\tan endless river
        of righteous living.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWas it to me you were bringing sacrifices and offerings during
        the forty years in the wilderness, Israel? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, you served your pagan gods\u2014Sakkuth your king god and Kaiwan
        your star god\u2014the images you made for yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will send you into exile, to a land east of Damascus,[COMMENT[0]]\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, whose name is the God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies."
      comments:
      - number: '5:26-27 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: "No, you carried your pagan gods\u2014the shrine of Molech, the star
            of your god Rephan, and the images you made for yourselves. So I will
            send you into exile, to a land east of Damascus. "
        - ft: Compare Acts 7:43.
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow awaits you who lounge in luxury in Jerusalem,[COMMENT[0]]and
        you who feel secure in Samaria!\n\tYou are famous and popular in Israel,\n\tand
        people go to you for help.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: in Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "But go over to Calneh\n\tand see what happened there.\n\tThen go
        to the great city of Hamath\n\tand down to the Philistine city of Gath.\n\tYou
        are no better than they were,\n\tand look at how they were destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You push away every thought of coming disaster,\n\tbut your actions
        only bring the day of judgment closer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How terrible for you who sprawl on ivory beds\n\tand lounge on your
        couches,\n\teating the meat of tender lambs from the flock\n\tand of choice
        calves fattened in the stall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You sing trivial songs to the sound of the harp\n\tand fancy yourselves
        to be great musicians like David.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You drink wine by the bowlful\n\tand perfume yourselves with fragrant
        lotions.\n\tYou care nothing about the ruin of your nation.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: of Joseph.
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, you will be the first to be led away as captives.\n\tSuddenly,
        all your parties will end.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
